value.0: This girl seems to be in the process of changing, clasping the last few bits of jewelry she needs across her wrists.
Aiko is fondly referred to as the "kindest, least discriminant" of the working girls  located in the cove, though the fact that she's blind is surely not related... The lads hope it isn't at least..

This lass's costume wings look decrepit and old. Though try as she might to keep them clean, it's clear she suffers from poor health.  Her somber expression leads her to be one of the least popular working girls of the Mermaid's Tail, but she continues to work herself exhausted.
This young lass sits in her performance chair busily adding the final touches to her blue costume paint, her legs constricted in a fake mermaid tail.  Pirates have the oddest fetishes.

This lass looks to be glowing with health, her tail flicking suggestively as she dances on stage.  Her seductive charm and charisma seem to keep the lads coming, leading her to be the most popular working girl in the Mermaid's Tail.

Lune is a tall, almost middle aged-woman with a high nose and sharp features.  Dressed lavishly, she gives an often cold stare to the men who come to her for her girl's services. Rumor has it that the last man who mistreated a girl of her's lost his member in an unfortunate smelting "accident."
This young lass looks to be barely eighteen.  Youthful and pale, she claims to never wear makeup.  But in her profession, that's almost assuredly a lie.

This lass looks to be an odd mixture of human, elf.. and something else. Exotic pointed eartips poke out of her hair, and should someone get close enough, small pin-feathers mingle within her flaxen tresses.

This voluptuous lass gives any lad she sees a cheeky wink as he walks her by, though it's hard to tell if she's winking or just blinking.  Why is she wearing a fake eyepatch and hat you ask? Why, she has the best and biggest booty of course!
Eric is a rough looking Tiefling.  His left horn is cracked in half, and he never seems to be cleanly shaven.  But his drinks are surprisingly well-made.
Gregory is a clean, well-dressed Tiefling.  He serves drinks with a flirtatious flair, offering a devilish wink every once in a while.
This young, well-shaven lad flashes a charming smile to any and all customers he sees fit to.  While only boredly offering a towel to those he doesnt seem so interested in talking to.
This portly woman holds herself with confidence and flaunts every back roll and love handle she has with pride. She insists upon being referred to as "Puddles," claiming that everyone does.
This rough-looking half-orc watches the door with his back leaned against the wall.  Occasionally, he'll adjust the wraps around his calloused hands.
This rough-looking half-orc watches the door with his back leaned against the wall.  Occasionally, he'll adjust the wraps around his calloused hands, when he's not busy oggling the girls, that is.

Value.value: Leaves from the wyssin plant are dried and rolled into a tobaccolike substance and smoked.

A pale pink liquour with a sweet, and mild taste.  A favorite among the girls at the Mermaid's Tail, many patrons regard it as a "girly" drink.  Yet still, the sales of it are too high to account for only women purchasing it...
